title: Starbucks opts for JPMorgan Chase division to replace payments partner Square
text: October 23, 2015 at 15:02 PM EDT Starbucks opts for JPMorgan Chase division to replace payments partner Square Starbucks has named a division of JPMorgan Chase & Co. as its new payments partner. Chase Commerce Solutions – the New York bank's global payment processing division – will process all non-mobile payments for Starbucks (Nasdaq: SBUX), replacing the credit card processing service Square, which Starbucks had used as its payments processing service since 2012...
